href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/7"}}, "title": "add an example with ExternalProject"}}, {"update": {"description": "I've added a minimal example of a package that uses ignition-cmake and calls `ign_configure_build` but goes no further. This requires CMakeLists.txt files to exist in the `doc`, `include`, `src`, and `test` folders.\r\n\r\nI also used `ExternalProject_Add` so that the examples will be built during `make`. I had to do two funky things in 08ccbf3 to allow the external project to `find_package(ignition-cmake0)` without actually installing `ignition-cmake`:\r\n\r\n* set the `CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH` in a cmake arg to the external project\r\n* create symlink in build folder to the `cmake` folder in the source. Since the `create_symlink` cmake command is [only supported on UNIX](https://cmake.org/cmake/help/v3.2/manual/cmake.1.html#unix-specific-command-line-tools), ~~the ExternalProject_Add call is also restricted to UNIX systems~~ the files are copied one-by-one for non-unix systems (25f8aee)", "title": "add an example with ExternalProject", "destination": {"commit": {"hash": "981c6eda3e1f", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/commit/981c6eda3e1f.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/commits/981c6eda3e1f"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3e77bcf7-f260-4cec-a1a0-116b8e298901}ts=default"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "ign-cmake", "full_name": "ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake", "uuid": "{3e77bcf7-f260-4cec-a1a0-116b8e298901}"}, "branch": {"name": "default"}}, "reason": "", "source": {"commit": {"hash": "adf3f61d58eb", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/commit/adf3f61d58eb.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/commits/adf3f61d58eb"}}}, "rep